description.text: Specifies the parent node/object handle on which the rsvp configuration should be configured. In case modes modify/delete/disable/enable this denotes the object node handle on which the action needs to be performed. The handle value syntax is dependent on the vendor.

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.
The number of RsvpIf to configure on the targeted Ixia interface. The range is 0-1000.
MAC address to be used for the first session.
Valid only for -mode create. The incrementing step for the MAC address configured on the dirrectly connected interfaces. Valid only when IxNetwork Tcl API is used.

Enables vlan on the directly connected ISIS router interface. Valid options are: 0 - disable, 1 - enable. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is an ISIS router handle.
For multiple neighbor configuration, configures the VLAN ID mode.

Valid only for -mode create. Defines the step for the VLAN ID when the VLAN ID mode is increment. When vlan_id_step causes the vlan_id value to exceed its maximum value the increment will be done modulo <number of possible vlan ids>. Examples: vlan_id = 4094; vlan_id_step = 2 -> new vlan_id value = 0 vlan_id = 4095; vlan_id_step = 11 -> new vlan_id value = 10
VLAN user priority assigned to protocol interface.

Interface IP address of the RSVP session router. Mandatory when -mode is create. When using IxTclNetwork (new API) this parameter can be omitted if -interface_handle is used. For IxTclProtocol (old API), when -mode is modify and one of the layer 2-3 parameters (-intf_ip_addr, -gateway_ip_addr, -loopback_ip_addr, etc) needs to be modified, the emulation_ldp_config command must be provided with the entire list of layer 2-3 parameters. Otherwise they will be set to their default values.
Define interface IP address for multiple sessions. Valid only for -mode create.
Gives the gateway IP address for the protocol interface that will be created for use by the simulated routers.
Valid only for -mode create. Gives the step for the gateway IP address.
Use Same Authentication Key for Peer
Generate Sequence Number Based on Real Time

returnValue.value: A list containing the ipv4 protocol stack handles that were added by the command (if any).
A list containing the ethernet protocol stack handles that were added by the command (if any).
When status is $::FAILURE, contains more information
